Vol / Page:  3
Edition:
Quote:  The Rocky River, Snow's rush, and the Kaituna diggings, have each of them a few parties, who are going on steadily; a larger population is all that is required to develop their riches; they have, in addition to the richness of their river beds, got large flats on their banks, which at no distant date will be the resort of capitalists, the work required to bring them into a producing state being above the means of any ordinary party of diggers.
